A magnitude 7.4 quake struck a few miles south of Izmit.
The death toll in the 7.4-magnitude quake has surpassed 12,000 and some officials have predicted as many as 40,000 could have died.
There have been 1,300 aftershocks in the region, dozens of which registered at four degrees or above.
According to the latest statistics, Kocaeli (Izmit) province posted the highest casualty as 5,179 bodies had been discovered and 14,718 people were injured.
Preliminary estimates have put direct economic loss of the quake at between 20 and 40 billion U.S. European seismologists have arrived in Turkey to study the quake.
